The SDD_DataStorage service exposed by the SEALDD Server enables a service consumer to:
-	create/update/delete/query a SEALDD Data Storage;
-	receive SEALDD Data Management and/or Status Information Notifications;
-	create/update/delete a SEALDD Data Storage Delivery Subscription;
-	receive SEALDD Data Storage Delivery Notifications; and
-	request for one-time SEALDD Data Storage delivery.
